ht="auto" title="Majnu ka Tila Gurudwara" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> An aerial view of Majnu ka Tila Gurudwara, a prominent Sikh temple in Delhi. </div> <div class="row mt-5"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/drone5-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/drone5-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/drone5-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/drone5.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="Yamuna River" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> An aerial view of the Yamuna River. </div> <div class="row mt-5"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/delhi_sahiba.JPG-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/delhi_sahiba.JPG-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/delhi_sahiba.JPG-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/delhi_sahiba.JPG" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="Sahiba River and Highway" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> An aerial view of the Sahiba River and a nearby highway. The river's surface is covered with toxic white foam, a stark reminder of the environmental challenges facing Delhi's waterways. This polluted river eventually drains into the larger Yamuna River. </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="recreational"/><category term="drone,"/><category term="photography,"/><category term="delhi"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A collection of Drone Shots from Delhi (My Hometown)]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Capturing India - A Photographic Journey</title><link href="https://sakshambhutani.xyz/blog/2020/photos_India/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Capturing India - A Photographic Journey"/><published>2020-07-15T15:09:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-07-15T15:09:00+00:00</updated><id>https://sakshambhutani.xyz/blog/2020/photos_India</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://sakshambhutani.xyz/blog/2020/photos_India/"><![CDATA[<p>I have had the opportunity to travel extensively across India. My travels have covered diverse regions, from the northernmost state of Jammu &amp; Kashmir to the southernmost state of Tamil Nadu, and from Gujarat in the west to Assam in the east. I‚Äôve explored mountainous regions like Uttarakhand, Himachal Pradesh, and Sikkim, coastal states such as Goa and Odisha, and inland areas including Madhya Pradesh and Telangana. These journeys have allowed me to experience India‚Äôs varied landscapes, cultures, and traditions firsthand. The following photos showcase some of the places I‚Äôve visited during these travels.</p> <blockquote class="block-warning"> <h5 id="note">NOTE</h5> <p>All the images are high resolution and might take a while to load.</p> </blockquote> <h2 id="-new-delhi">üìç New Delhi</h2> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/good1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/good1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/good1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/good1.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="Connaught Place" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> The bustling Connaught Place in the heart of New Delhi. </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/good12-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/good12-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/good12-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/good12.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="India Gate" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> India Gate (clicked from Copernicus Marg), a war memorial in the center of New Delhi. </div> <h3 id="diwali-celebrations-at-home">Diwali Celebrations at Home</h3> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/good2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/good2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/good2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/good2.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="Diwali Diya" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Illuminating diyas (oil lamps) during Diwali, the festival of lights. </div> <div class="row mt-4"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/good3-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/good3-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/good3-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/good3.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="Collection of Diyas" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Rangoli (floor art) with diyas for Diwali. </div> <div class="row mt-4"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex align-items-center"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/good8-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/good8-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/good8-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/good8.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" title="Chakri Firecr